{"type":"message","id":"ba0c947a","parentId":"03309f8f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:00.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the pulse log and the mutation.","thinkingSignature":"d95bc182bf1606288f066b07f765e947f55e8c0568643ecf80c7bc39020e6c6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j0pngdvd8jvs_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 002914.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j0pngdvd8jvs_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 002914.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":745,"output":110,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12809,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326597785}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb371dfa","parentId":"ba0c947a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:00.442Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j0pngdvd8jvs_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 002914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or start working on one of the pending items like PowerShell wrapper, significance scoring, or tuning λ\r\n\r\nGiven the insight about compression-causal duality, implementing the TIC classifier seems like the most aligned action. But implementing a full classifier might be too much for one pulse.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what would be a good single concrete action:\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 002713.md`\r\n\r\nA good concrete action could be:\r\n1. Create a simple TIC experiment script/prototype\r\n2. Start documenting the TIC algorithm in the research folder\r\n3. Create a simple invariant detector based on pulse logs\r\n\r\nGiven the constraint of one action per pulse, I should pick something focused. Let me create the initial TIC experiment implementation or documentation.\r\n\r\nActually, let me check what's already in the research folder and logs folder to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nThe most specific next action from the goals is:\r\n\"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\"\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete task. I could:\r\n1. Create a Python/PowerShell script to analyze pulse logs for invariants\r\n2. Create documentation for the TIC algorithm\r\n3. Start the actual classification experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create a focused script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts content\r\n3. Identifies invariants vs variants\r\n\r\nThis would be a good single concrete action that advances the TIC experiment goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step, requiring a classifier to identify invariants across pulse logs. A focused script to extract and analyze pulse content patterns is needed before running the full experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that reads recent pulse logs, extracts text content, and identifies invariant vs variant patterns using n-gram overlap scoring. This provides the foundation for the TIC experiment validation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nIdentifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs\r\nPart of: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY experiment\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_NGRAM_LENGTH = 2\r\nMAX_NGRAM_LENGTH = 5\r\n\r\ndef extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful text from pulse markdown file.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(pulse_path, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Remove markdown formatting, keep headers and content\r\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\r\n    text_lines = [l for l in lines if l.startswith('#') or (l.strip() and not l.startswith('```'))]\r\n    return ' '.join(text_lines)\r\n\r\ndef get_ngrams(text, n):\r\n    \"\"\"Generate n-grams from text.\"\"\"\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return set(' '.join(words[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(words)-n+1))\r\n\r\ndef compute_overlap(set1, set2):\r\n    \"\"\"Jaccard similarity between two sets.\"\"\"\r\n    if not set1 or not set2:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    intersection = len(set1 & set2)\r\n    union = len(set1 | set2)\r\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse_pair(pulse1_text, pulse2_text):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify relationship between two consecutive pulses.\r\n    Returns: (classification, confidence)\r\n    classification: 'invariant' if high overlap, 'variant' if low overlap\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    scores = []\r\n    for n in range(MIN_NGRAM_LENGTH, MAX_NGRAM_LENGTH + 1):\r\n        ngrams1 = get_ngrams(pulse1_text, n)\r\n        ngrams2 = get_ngrams(pulse2_text, n)\r\n        scores.append(compute_overlap(ngrams1, ngrams2))\r\n    \r\n    avg_score = sum(scores) / len(scores)\r\n    \r\n    # Threshold: >0.4 overlap = invariant (causal/structural continuity)\r\n    classification = 'invariant' if avg_score > 0.4 else 'variant'\r\n    return classification, avg_score\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment(num_pulses=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:num_pulses]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 2:\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Insufficient pulse files\"}\r\n    \r\n    results = {\r\n        'total_pairs': 0,\r\n        'invariant_count': 0,\r\n        'variant_count': 0,\r\n        'avg_confidence': 0.0,\r\n        'pairs': []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    total_confidence = 0.0\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulse_files) - 1):\r\n        text1 = extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_files[i])\r\n        text2 = extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_files[i+1])\r\n        \r\n        classification, confidence = classify_pulse_pair(text1, text2)\r\n        \r\n        results['pairs'].append({\r\n            'pulse1': pulse_files\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:29:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326600441}}
{"type":"message","id":"3955fa3a","parentId":"cb371dfa","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:00.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j0pngdvd8jvs_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"scripts/tic_classifier.py\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\nIdentifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs\nPart of: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY experiment\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\nMIN_NGRAM_LENGTH = 2\nMAX_NGRAM_LENGTH = 5\n\ndef extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_path):\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful text from pulse markdown file.\"\"\"\n    with open(pulse_path, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    # Remove markdown formatting, keep headers and content\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\n    text_lines = [l for l in lines if l.startswith('#') or (l.strip() and not l.startswith('```'))]\n    return ' '.join(text_lines)\n\ndef get_ngrams(text, n):\n    \"\"\"Generate n-grams from text.\"\"\"\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\n    return set(' '.join(words[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(words)-n+1))\n\ndef compute_overlap(set1, set2):\n    \"\"\"Jaccard similarity between two sets.\"\"\"\n    if not set1 or not set2:\n        return 0.0\n    intersection = len(set1 & set2)\n    union = len(set1 | set2)\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\n\ndef classify_pulse_pair(pulse1_text, pulse2_text):\n    \"\"\"\n    Classify relationship between two consecutive pulses.\n    Returns: (classification, confidence)\n    classification: 'invariant' if high overlap, 'variant' if low overlap\n    \"\"\"\n    scores = []\n    for n in range(MIN_NGRAM_LENGTH, MAX_NGRAM_LENGTH + 1):\n        ngrams1 = get_ngrams(pulse1_text, n)\n        ngrams2 = get_ngrams(pulse2_text, n)\n        scores.append(compute_overlap(ngrams1, ngrams2))\n    \n    avg_score = sum(scores) / len(scores)\n    \n    # Threshold: >0.4 overlap = invariant (causal/structural continuity)\n    classification = 'invariant' if avg_score > 0.4 else 'variant'\n    return classification, avg_score\n\ndef run_tic_experiment(num_pulses=20):\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\n    pulse_files = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:num_pulses]\n    \n    if len(pulse_files) < 2:\n        return {\"error\": \"Insufficient pulse files\"}\n    \n    results = {\n        'total_pairs': 0,\n        'invariant_count': 0,\n        'variant_count': 0,\n        'avg_confidence': 0.0,\n        'pairs': []\n    }\n    \n    total_confidence = 0.0\n    \n    for i in range(len(pulse_files) - 1):\n        text1 = extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_files[i])\n        text2 = extract_text_from_pulse(pulse_files[i+1])\n        \n        classification, confidence = classify_pulse_pair(text1, text2)\n        \n        results['pairs'].append({\n            'pulse1': pulse_files\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326600443}}
